adjectives.description: overbuilt (comparative more overbuilt, superlative most overbuilt)

definitionGroups.group: Having had excessive construction (building) carried out, as:

examples: in the overbuilt exurbs of the megalopolis

entries.meaning: (mechanical devices, buildings) Built for heavier duty than might be predicted to be necessary.
examples: the extra wind protection provided by the overbuilt framing

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of overbuild
